      "text": "PharoEDA is a framework that simplifies developing Event-Driven Architectures [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Event-driven_architecture wikipedia]. It's also an opinionated framework favoring Domain-Driven Design [2], which means that if you honor some conventions, and the adapters are available, PharoEDA will let you focus in your domain and only in your domain. It works out-of-the-box. Please read on even if your programming language of choice is not Pharo Smalltalk [3]. [https://github.com/osoco/pharo-eda#event-driven-architectures-in-pharo github]\n"
    },
